omic—making Anger, Mercy, Revenge a work just as complicated, astute, and ambitious as its author.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aKaster, Robert A.1 aNussbaum, Martha C.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226748535423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226748535.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles